column5: Just thought I would share this with you, yesterday I got 101 pictures done at walmart and only paid 19 cents. Basically sign up a new account on their photocentre website HERE and you get 50 free 4x6s. Then with this code fsi50bonus you get another 50 free. Just upload pics and they are ready in an hour
Good find Dan thanks for the info.   Art

Thanks for posting this Dan...  My printer (Lexmark 3470) always has a green tint to any pics I print even on Photo quality paper  I was hoping to get some decent prints to take to Jack's (Nanook) Celebration of Life Memorial at Buckhorn Community Centre next Sunday 19 Jan 2011...

Cool stuff, my dad want's me to print off lot's of pictures of out summer trips these last 2 years while the pictures are still safe on my computer. Printed pictures at WalMart before and was pleased with those Kodak machines...just got to be patient and wait for the lines of people printing here in Oshawa.  MTBF
Thanks for the tip.
Hey thanks for that Dan!
You can even e-mail your pics in and then you only have to stand in line to pick up your prints. Or you can have them mailed to you and then you don't have to go there at all.
Yep pretty slick.   I can not find out where to put the bonus code in though.
It's on the final page of the checkout

Hey Dan! I wanted to personally thank-you for posting this link! I just sent in 100 pics and dont have to pay a red cent for them..How awesome is that! Grimace when you upload the 100 pics and go to the checkout they ask for the bomus code..Enter it there.. Awesome find Dan. You da MAN!!!!
Awesome.  Thanks Dan.  You rule
Done and done.  Thanks Dan.
*SMILES*
Thanks for the info!! 115 pics for $2.85.
If you want high quality reproductions (ie you're going to frame them) don't get them at Walmart.  You get what you pay for unfortunately.
anyone else having issue with the preview  not working?  Thanks for the heads up Dan .
I can't speak for myself because I print my own stuff, but in several photography forums that I frequent, Walmarts photo lab is often highly recommended by posters that live for photography.

Doesn't work for me either.  Click on it and nothing happens. I've seen this happen on other posts too.

where do we enter the coupon code?
Look up Gerritt.  The boys had to explain it to me as well.  At the checkout.
